The paper discusses self-play algorithms in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on competitive reinforcement learning, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions Markov games, which are a type of stochastic control system (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.GT, cs.MA, and cs.SY.
